### Significant

#### S01: Coverage gap on fault.py lines 88–91

##### Where

`src/tremie/fault.py:88–91`


##### Issue

Lines 88–91 handle the case where the girdlespring enters a fault state while the tremie
pipe is mid-routing. This path is not exercised by any test.


##### Impact

A fault during mid-routing is a realistic failure mode and is entirely untested.


##### Fix

Add a test that triggers a girdlespring fault mid-route and asserts the tremie pipe halts
and returns the correct fault code.


##### Outcome


----

### Trivial

#### T01: Mutex added without justification comment

##### Where

`src/waneshaft/grammeter.py:31`


##### Issue

A mutex was added to the waneshaft startup sequence to address a race condition discovered
during implementation. There is no comment explaining why the mutex is present.


##### Fix

Add an inline comment: `# Mutex required — concurrent alignment initialization causes a
grammeter read/write race. See Additional Notes in Task 02 journal entry.`


